Memory Map
---
- 0x0000 - 0x00FF   : Stack
- 0x0100 - 0x8FFF   : RAM
- 0x9000 - 0xEFFF   : ROM
- 0xF000 - 0xFFFD   : Unused
- 0xFFFE - 0xFFFF   : Program Start Pointer

Instructions
---
- A Register Manipulation
  - 0x01 : LDA
    - Load A register with next value in memory
  - 0x02 : STA
    - Stores A register at location specified from next two memory cells
  - 0x03 : ADA
    - Adds next memory cell to A register
  - 0x04 : SBA
    - Subtracts next memory cell from A register
- X Register Manipulation
  - 0x11 : LDX
    - Load X register with next value in memory
  - 0x12 : STX
    - Stores X register at location specified from next two memory cells
  - 0x13 : ADX
    - Adds next memory cell to X register
  - 0x14 : SBX
    - Subtracts next memory cell from X register
- Y Register Manipulation
  - 0x21 : LDY
    - Load Y register with next value in memory
  - 0x22 : STY
    - Stores Y register at location specified from next two memory cells
  - 0x23 : ADY
    - Adds next memory cell to Y register
  - 0x24 : SBY
    - Subtracts next memory cell from Y register
- Flow Control
  - 0x00 : NOP
    - No Operation
  - 0x30 : JMP
    - Jumps the PC to the location specified from next two memory cells
  - 0x31 : JSR*
    - Pushes PC to stack and jumps to a subroutine 
  - 0x32 : RSR*
    - Pops PC from stack and returns from subroutine
###### *not implemented